1
00:00:09,439 --> 00:00:10,759
Your time is up too.

2
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,760
Hello, Uncle Li.

3
00:01:10,599 --> 00:01:11,439
Good girl, Yaya.

4
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:13,359
You still remember me.

5
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,280
You two head home first.

6
00:01:18,439 --> 00:01:19,799
Captain Li, I'll let you two talk.

7
00:01:19,799 --> 00:01:21,040
I'll take her home now.

8
00:01:23,439 --> 00:01:24,400
Ride safely, okay?

9
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,599
Let me know when you're home.

10
00:01:25,959 --> 00:01:26,680
Say goodbye to Uncle Li.

11
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:27,840
Goodbye, Uncle Li.

12
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,560
Bye, Yaya.

13
00:01:29,200 --> 00:01:29,719
We're off now.

14
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:30,480
Take care, Sister-in-law.

15
00:01:41,439 --> 00:01:42,480
How is Yaya's health?

16
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:48,239
She's pretty much recovered.

17
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,959
She even got an award recently.

18
00:01:52,599 --> 00:01:53,239
Really?

19
00:01:54,599 --> 00:01:55,439
Model Student.

20
00:01:55,599 --> 00:01:57,400
Though the award is now called

21
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,760
Outstanding Student.

22
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:01,840
That's wonderful.

23
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,760
I'm closing up here.

24
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:13,879
I haven't eaten all day.

25
00:02:16,159 --> 00:02:16,800
I'm starving.

26
00:02:17,879 --> 00:02:18,680
No problem.

27
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,680
But every time you eat here,

28
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,360
you always pay way too much.

29
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:23,400
Today's different.

30
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:27,560
Today I'm here to dine and dash.

31
00:02:29,039 --> 00:02:29,599
Noodles.

32
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,080
However many bowls you want,

33
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:32,439
I'll cook them all for you.

34
00:02:33,439 --> 00:02:34,520
If it were anything else,

35
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,479
I really couldn't help you.

36
00:02:39,479 --> 00:02:40,520
You've been away from the squad

37
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,479
helping your wife run this shop for months.

38
00:02:43,879 --> 00:02:46,439
Don't you miss life on the squad at all?

39
00:02:48,199 --> 00:02:50,560
Don't you miss your brothers there?

40
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,400
I've been too busy making a living

41
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,280
to think about any of that.

42
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,199
Have a seat.

43
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,159
I'll go cook you a bowl of noodles.

44
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:22,479
Captain Li.

45
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,360
Here.

46
00:03:23,960 --> 00:03:24,759
Noodles are ready.

47
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:31,199
Here you go.

48
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:38,680
These noodles today,

49
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:41,719
something's off about them.

50
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:42,719
Really?

51
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:44,599
That can't be.

52
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,639
Same old recipe.

53
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:51,719
I remember when Captain Zhao was around,

54
00:03:51,719 --> 00:03:52,840
he often took us out for noodles.

55
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,120
He always picked up the tab.

56
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:58,840
Everything tasted so good back then.

57
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,560
Because of the brotherhood, right?

58
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,199
But these noodles today,

59
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,199
maybe it's because

60
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,319
our brother's gone.

61
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,199
I remember one time,

62
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,000
the three of us were having noodles.

63
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,000
Captain Zhao asked us,

64
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,000
"Tasty?"

65
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:28,399
We both said yes.

66
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,800
Captain Zhao asked, "Why?"

67
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:34,519
I said because I was hungry.

68
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:35,920
You said because there was a lot of meat.

69
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:40,439
Remember what Captain Zhao said?

70
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,439
How is it? Tasty?

71
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,199
Delicious.

72
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,319
Really delicious.

73
00:04:57,079 --> 00:04:58,480
Know why it's so good?

74
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,639
We're hungry.

75
00:04:59,959 --> 00:05:01,279
Because my noodles have lots of meat.

76
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:06,160
There is plenty of meat, sure.

77
00:05:06,959 --> 00:05:08,519
But the main reason

78
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,040
is that this bowl of noodles holds

79
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:14,399
the taste of our shared fight for justice.

80
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,439
See how high-minded your Boss is.

81
00:05:17,839 --> 00:05:19,120
You'd better learn from him.

82
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,720
I believe you haven't forgotten.

83
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,000
Captain Li.

84
00:05:28,759 --> 00:05:29,639
Please, stop.

85
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:33,079
All I want now is a quiet, simple life.

86
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,439
Some things,

87
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,240
buried inside won't just fade away.

88
00:05:50,399 --> 00:05:51,600
They might just keep getting heavier,

89
00:05:52,959 --> 00:05:54,439
weighing on you so you never sleep again.

90
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,079
But...

91
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:59,399
I just want to protect my family.

92
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,720
But it requires one thing.

93
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,040
You have to be alive.

94
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:05,319
Captain Li,

95
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:07,240
what do you mean by that?

96
00:06:08,879 --> 00:06:10,120
Don't call me Captain Li anymore.

97
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,279
Before I walked through this door today,

98
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,480
I was already a fugitive.

99
00:06:26,399 --> 00:06:27,839
I came today just to tell you,

100
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,600
the one who paid you off is a devil.

101
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:31,040
What is the devil's rule?

102
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:33,439
Only the dead can keep secrets.

103
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,399
Stop pushing me.

104
00:06:34,399 --> 00:06:36,319
I really don't know anything.

105
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,240
Fine.

106
00:06:45,959 --> 00:06:46,879
We agreed earlier,

107
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,319
it's your treat today.

108
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,199
I don't want to owe you a favor.

109
00:06:53,079 --> 00:06:54,120
Here's a gift.

110
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:57,879
My new number is on this.

111
00:07:19,519 --> 00:07:20,319
Captain Zhao.

112
00:07:22,319 --> 00:07:23,279
I've let you down.

113
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:14,279
Sorry about this,

114
00:08:14,439 --> 00:08:15,399
we're closing up.

115
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,279
Your time is up.

116
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:10,720
Need a room.

117
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,039
Single's fifty.

118
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,399
Double's eighty, with a shower.

119
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,039
Single. ID, please. ID.

120
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,559
Your ID.

121
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:22,679
Lost it.

122
00:10:23,519 --> 00:10:24,559
Then I can't check you in.

123
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:28,039
Hey.

124
00:10:29,279 --> 00:10:30,759
You look kind of familiar.

125
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,039
How about 150? Can I stay?

126
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,519
Here. Room 301.

127
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:48,600
Thanks.

128
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,200
Hey, you forgot your change!

129
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,320
Bread and beer.

130
00:11:07,919 --> 00:11:08,440
Thanks.

131
00:11:34,399 --> 00:11:35,360
Oh my God.

132
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,399
Keep your eyes peeled.

133
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,600
You all know what the target is capable of.

134
00:12:30,159 --> 00:12:30,799
Captain Wang.

135
00:12:31,159 --> 00:12:32,679
My Boss must have been framed.

136
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,000
Cut the crap.

137
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:36,120
He's not your Boss anymore.

138
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,320
He's a fugitive.

139
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,000
Check your weapons.

140
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,000
Do we really need guns?

141
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:42,200
Yeah, Captain Wang.

142
00:12:42,399 --> 00:12:43,600
Captain Li isn't even armed.

143
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,559
One more word and you're off this op.

144
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:48,679
Move out.

145
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:47,720
Captain Wang.

146
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:49,720
Nothing.

147
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:54,240
Fall back.
